cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.NE, cs.RO 

The paper proposes a reinforcement learning approach to solve combinatorial optimization problems on a graph. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the use of graph theory and algorithms, which could place it under the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper uses neural networks to learn heuristics for solving the optimization problem, which could place it under the category of neural networks (cs.NE).
